<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1991</TIMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Prusiner</ENAMEX> reported at a major conference that he had proved that the
infectious <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">agents</ENAMEX> of these <ENAMEX TYPE="DISEASE">diseases</ENAMEX> were proteins free of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">nucleic acids</ENAMEX>. In
particular, he had created <ENAMEX TYPE="ANIMAL">mice</ENAMEX> with a genetic mutation that caused what was a
